		 	<span id="comment_score_64357672" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64357672); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>2</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~RossCWilliams">RossCWilliams</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~RossCWilliams">( 5513152 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64357672"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64357672">Its called a plug-in hybrid. It gives you both electric for most of your trips and range for longer trips. PHEV's  also have a lower emission footprint to build than an BEV because it requires smaller batteries. Which is also the problem with using two different vehicles. You have more emissions to build two vehicles than to build only one. Better yet, walk, ride a bike, take transit or catch a ride with someone else. Those all are going to reduce emissions more than driving your electric SOV.</div>
	</div>

